	<h2 class="title"><a href="http://wearechange.org/activists-call-un-intervention-government-moves-shut-water-detroits-broke-residents/" title="Permanent Link to Activists Call For UN Intervention As Government Moves To Shut Off Water For Detroit’s Broke Residents">Activists Call For UN Intervention As Government Moves To Shut Off Water For Detroit’s Broke Residents</a></h2>



	
		
	<p class="post-meta"><img src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2d6d461504b45fe4c2b5ab0325d5e0fb?s=50&amp;d=&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-50 avatar-default' height='50' width='50' style='width: 50px; height: 50px;' alt='avatar' />Posted  by <a href="http://wearechange.org/author/alecope88/" title="Posts by alecope88" rel="author">alecope88</a> on June 22, 2014</p>


	


	


	<p><a href="http://thinkprogress.org/economy/2014/06/20/3451488/detroit-water-shutoffs-complaint/" target="_blank">www.thinkprogress.org</a></p>
<p><img class="alignnone" src="http://thinkprogress.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/shutterstock_74527048-638x410.jpg" alt="" width="638" height="410" /></p>
<p>As the Detroit Water and Sewerage Department moves to <a href="http://www.mintpressnews.com/groups-appeal-to-un-to-stop-water-cut-offs-in-detroit-and-restore-basic-human-rights/192731/" target="_blank">shut off water to thousands of residents</a> who are delinquent on their bills, a coalition of activists is appealing to the United Nations High Commission for Human Rights to intervene on behalf of the bankrupt city’s most vulnerable citizens.</p>
<p>Their <a href="http://www.blueplanetproject.net/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/Detroit-HRTW-submission-June-18-2014.pdf" target="_blank">report</a>, filed Wednesday with the UN’s Special Rapporteur on the Human Right to Safe Drinking Water and Sanitation, alleges that the DWSD crackdown is part of an effort “to sweeten the pot for a private investor” to take over the city’s heavily-indebted water and sewer system as part of <a href="http://thinkprogress.org/economy/2013/08/02/2408081/detroit-pension-explainer/" target="_blank">Detroit’s broader</a> bankruptcy proceedings.</p>


        <!-- AddThis Button END -->

<a class="readmore" href="http://wearechange.org/activists-call-un-intervention-government-moves-shut-water-detroits-broke-residents/"><img src="http://wearechange.org/wp-content/themes/Minimal/images/readmore_01.gif" class="mouseover" data-oversrc="http://wearechange.org/wp-content/themes/Minimal/images/readmore_02.gif" /></a>



